&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Indeed.

00:03:04.060 --> 00:03:05.060
Okay, so let's start with Pearls Deluxe.

00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:12.470
Now, Pearls Deluxe is a game that reminds
me a lot of something I've seen before.

00:03:12.470 --> 00:03:16.200
Did we play Pearls the non-Deluxe version
at some point, or?

00:03:16.200 --> 00:03:17.750
&gt;&gt;Galpin: I don't know.

00:03:17.750 --> 00:03:22.120
I thought you were going to say, "Pearls Deluxe
has got the most washed out looking feature

00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:23.563
graphic that I've ever seen."

00:03:23.563 --> 00:03:24.563
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: That is an issue, yeah.

00:03:24.563 --> 00:03:29.650
You may-- A lot of things about this feature
graphic are good.

00:03:29.650 --> 00:03:30.650
It's definitely legible.

00:03:30.650 --> 00:03:31.650
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Yeah.

00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:32.650
Yeah.

00:03:32.650 --> 00:03:33.650
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: But it's-- it could maybe--

00:03:33.650 --> 00:03:35.970
&gt;&gt;Galpin: It looks like it's been-- Not only
does it look washed out, but also, it looks

00:03:35.970 --> 00:03:39.070
like it's just been scaled up rather than
scaled down, which--

00:03:39.070 --> 00:03:40.260
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Oh, really?

