&gt;&gt;Galpin: Yeah.

00:03:41.260 --> 00:03:42.990
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Well, that may actually be my
fault.

00:03:42.990 --> 00:03:44.600
I may have actually put it on a different
resolution.

00:03:44.600 --> 00:03:47.390
&gt;&gt;Galpin: No, no, I looked at it on Google.

00:03:47.390 --> 00:03:48.390
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Oh, okay.

00:03:48.390 --> 00:03:49.390
All right.

00:03:49.390 --> 00:03:50.390
&gt;&gt;Galpin: It's kinda fuzzy looking.

00:03:50.390 --> 00:03:51.390
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: All right.

00:03:51.390 --> 00:03:54.010
So obviously, a great feature graphic is important.

00:03:54.010 --> 00:03:56.990
But it's particularly important if you want
to get featured.

00:03:56.990 --> 00:03:57.990
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Yes.

00:03:57.990 --> 00:03:59.730
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Now, let's talk about Pearls Deluxe.

00:03:59.730 --> 00:04:03.400
So Pearls Deluxe ended up being a really fun
game, I think.

00:04:03.400 --> 00:04:04.520
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Absolutely.

00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:06.750
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Do you play it much?

00:04:06.750 --> 00:04:08.290
Oh, it doesn't support--

00:04:08.290 --> 00:04:09.940
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Yeah, we're going to play--

00:04:09.940 --> 00:04:11.410
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: We're going to just put this down,
I think.

00:04:11.410 --> 00:04:14.740
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Play it like that, just so we don't
jiggle the HDMI, 'cause it's-- Okay.

00:04:14.740 --> 00:04:15.740
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Yep.

00:04:15.740 --> 00:04:16.740
Oh, that's funny.

00:04:16.740 --> 00:04:19.350
I put it down at an angle, and then I looked
at this, and I thought, "Oh no!

00:04:19.350 --> 00:04:20.350
How-- wait.

00:04:20.350 --> 00:04:21.519
How is that at an angle?"

00:04:21.519 --> 00:04:23.270
And it's just the way it works.

00:04:23.270 --> 00:04:25.660
So yeah.

00:04:25.660 --> 00:04:31.740
Pearls Deluxe is a-- it's a slight twist on
your typical bubble popping game.

00:04:31.740 --> 00:04:32.740
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Yeah.

00:04:32.740 --> 00:04:34.669
Actually, I think it's a pretty significant
twist.

00:04:34.669 --> 00:04:42.990
Basically, what you have to do is create sequences
of paths that have to cover all of the dots--

00:04:42.990 --> 00:04:49.741
you can't-- all of the pearls that are the
same color that are touching each other, but

00:04:49.741 --> 00:04:56.680
also have to be in a line that goes straight
through without any turns or diagonals.

00:04:56.680 --> 00:04:58.650
So, it's impossible to pick up--

00:04:58.650 --> 00:04:59.650
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Well, without any backtracking,
yes.

00:04:59.650 --> 00:05:00.650
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Without any backtracking.

00:05:00.650 --> 00:05:01.650
It's impossible.

00:05:01.650 --> 00:05:02.650
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: So for instance, this one you
can't do.

00:05:02.650 --> 00:05:03.650
&gt;&gt;Galpin: You can't do.

00:05:03.650 --> 00:05:04.650
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Uh-uh!

00:05:04.650 --> 00:05:05.650
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Uh-uh!

00:05:05.650 --> 00:05:06.650
Exactly.

00:05:06.650 --> 00:05:07.650
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: And they have a really, really
cute sound effects that we can't play because

00:05:07.650 --> 00:05:08.650
of the man.

00:05:08.650 --> 00:05:09.650
All right.

00:05:09.650 --> 00:05:10.650
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Exactly.

00:05:10.650 --> 00:05:12.139
Ooh, there's a big one over there on the--

00:05:12.139 --> 00:05:13.139
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: There is?

00:05:13.139 --> 00:05:14.139
Oh, let's see.

00:05:14.139 --> 00:05:15.139
Ooooh, yeah.

00:05:15.139 --> 00:05:16.139
Nice!

00:05:16.139 --> 00:05:17.139
Okay.

00:05:17.139 --> 00:05:18.139
Yeah.

00:05:18.139 --> 00:05:23.629
So what I like about this twist is that it's
not just a change in the way it's played from

00:05:23.629 --> 00:05:25.099
a mechanics level.

00:05:25.099 --> 00:05:27.639
It does affect your strategy deeply.

00:05:27.639 --> 00:05:28.870
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Yeah, absolutely.

00:05:28.870 --> 00:05:33.620
And it's-- You can definitely screw yourself
up and get to a point where's there's just

00:05:33.620 --> 00:05:36.450
nothing you can pop anymore, if you're not
careful.

00:05:36.450 --> 00:05:39.539
Also, there's a timer throughout the game,
as we just saw.

00:05:39.539 --> 00:05:41.719
So just some general comments about the game:
1.

00:05:41.719 --> 00:05:46.009
This is an example of what happens when you
don't actually look at the ad on a tablet

00:05:46.009 --> 00:05:47.009
device.

00:05:47.009 --> 00:05:48.539
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Yeah.

00:05:48.539 --> 00:05:51.300
Your ad network is probably not going to be
happy with you for that.

00:05:51.300 --> 00:05:55.561
&gt;&gt;Galpin: I think it's more of a-- You're
probably-- People aren't even going to know

00:05:55.561 --> 00:05:56.689
that it is-- Maybe they'll get some clicks
that way, I don't know.

00:05:56.689 --> 00:05:59.620
But I suspect you'll get fewer clicks if people
can't read the ad.

00:05:59.620 --> 00:06:00.939
But you never know.

00:06:00.939 --> 00:06:02.479
I never know what really works with these
things.

00:06:02.479 --> 00:06:05.280
So that's definitely one thing to look at.

00:06:05.280 --> 00:06:06.669
Now, what is the share button do?

00:06:06.669 --> 00:06:07.870
I didn't actually try it.

00:06:07.870 --> 00:06:08.990
I'm a little bit terrified.

00:06:08.990 --> 00:06:10.470
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Well, that is a share intent,
actually.

00:06:10.470 --> 00:06:11.840
&gt;&gt;Galpin: It is a share intent.

00:06:11.840 --> 00:06:12.840
That's good.

00:06:12.840 --> 00:06:15.160
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: But you've also got a Facebook
button.

00:06:15.160 --> 00:06:18.440
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Which takes you to the website.

00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:19.440
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Yeah.

00:06:19.440 --> 00:06:20.520
We're not super thrilled with that.

00:06:20.520 --> 00:06:26.009
And let me be really clear: it has nothing
to do with the particular social network.

00:06:26.009 --> 00:06:30.560
If this was a Google+ button, we would feel
exactly the same way.

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:38.249
It's just [pause] there's already a share
intent, and adding extra stuff on there, especially

00:06:38.249 --> 00:06:41.810
something that's going to take you out of
the game and launch a web browser, which is

00:06:41.810 --> 00:06:45.720
almost always going to take a long time to
start up, and it uses battery, and it uses

00:06:45.720 --> 00:06:46.720
data.

00:06:46.720 --> 00:06:47.720
Why?

00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:51.800
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Yeah, it's one of the things where
it's also a question of where you want to

00:06:51.800 --> 00:06:53.870
actually launch it in an external browser,
launch it in a web view.

00:06:53.870 --> 00:06:56.309
I don't even know what you wanted to do in
this case.

00:06:56.309 --> 00:07:00.990
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Yeah, it's like-- And the thing
is, part of it is the fact that there's already

00:07:00.990 --> 00:07:04.909
the share intent available, but I understand
that there's a difference between liking something

00:07:04.909 --> 00:07:07.240
or +1ing something and sharing it.

00:07:07.240 --> 00:07:12.599
But if you look at how these buttons work
on websites, when you +1 something, or when

00:07:12.599 --> 00:07:15.340
you like something, that's a single action.

00:07:15.340 --> 00:07:17.520
You just press that button and you're done.

00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:19.879
It's supposed to be a very, very lightweight
action.

00:07:19.879 --> 00:07:22.659
But here, you've changed something that's
supposed to be lightweight, and you've made

00:07:22.659 --> 00:07:24.100
it extremely heavyweight.

00:07:24.100 --> 00:07:25.449
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Exactly, exactly.

00:07:25.449 --> 00:07:27.270
I completely agree with you.

00:07:27.270 --> 00:07:30.190
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Basically, I liked you when I
press that button, but by the time the web

00:07:30.190 --> 00:07:32.449
browser launched, I no longer like you.

00:07:32.449 --> 00:07:33.470
&gt;&gt;Galpin: Exactly.

00:07:33.470 --> 00:07:37.699
You just have to be that much more enthusiastic
about the game to actually get to the liking

00:07:37.699 --> 00:07:38.699
phase.

00:07:38.699 --> 00:07:39.699
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: Exactly.

00:07:39.699 --> 00:07:40.699
It is a pretty good game, though.

00:07:40.699 --> 00:07:42.860
&gt;&gt;Galpin: It is, it is.

00:07:42.860 --> 00:07:45.930
In general, it behaves reasonably well.

00:07:45.930 --> 00:07:47.590
Nothing wrong with this.

00:07:47.590 --> 00:07:48.729
&gt;&gt;Ni-Lewis: All right.

00:07:48.729 --> 00:07:53.169
&gt;&gt;Galpin: So in terms of what happens when
you press the back key here.

00:07:53.169 --> 00:07:54.719
Reasonable.

00:07:54.719 --> 00:07:58.360
Again, it looks like a dialog, and there we
are.

00:07:58.360 --> 00:07:59.360
Back at our home screen.

00:07:59.360 --> 00:08:00.360
So not too bad.

